WEBVTT

00:02.959 --> 00:06.875
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

00:02.959 --> 00:06.875
<i>Stardate 41798.2.</i>

00:06.917 --> 00:08.792
<i>We have been ordered</i>

00:06.917 --> 00:08.792
<i>by Starfleet</i>

00:08.834 --> 00:10.792
<i>to proceed</i>

00:08.834 --> 00:10.792
<i>to the Lorenze Cluster</i>

00:10.834 --> 00:12.750
<i>and investigate</i>

00:10.834 --> 00:12.750
<i>the disappearance</i>

00:12.792 --> 00:14.959
<i>of the light cruiser</i>

00:12.792 --> 00:14.959
<i>U.S.S.</i> Drake--

00:15.000 --> 00:16.417
<i>which was in that system</i>

00:16.458 --> 00:18.834
<i>trying to unravel</i>

00:16.458 --> 00:18.834
<i>a mystery of its own</i>

00:18.875 --> 00:21.291
<i>which began when recent</i>

00:18.875 --> 00:21.291
<i>long-range probes</i>

00:21.333 --> 00:24.625
<i>indicated that all intelligent</i>

00:21.333 --> 00:24.625
<i>life on the planet Minos</i>

00:24.667 --> 00:26.834
<i>had disappeared.</i>

00:28.500 --> 00:29.709
Number One?

00:29.750 --> 00:31.750
No help from

00:29.750 --> 00:31.750
the communications log, sir.

00:31.792 --> 00:33.667
The<i> Drake</i> reported

00:31.792 --> 00:33.667
arriving at Minos

00:33.709 --> 00:35.208
and then wasn't

00:33.709 --> 00:35.208
heard from again.

00:35.250 --> 00:36.417
Mr. Data?

00:36.458 --> 00:39.333
The citizens of

00:36.458 --> 00:39.333
Minos gained fame

00:39.375 --> 00:41.750
during the Esalrope Wars

00:39.375 --> 00:41.750
as arms merchants.

00:41.792 --> 00:43.375
They manufactured

00:41.792 --> 00:43.375
sophisticated

00:43.417 --> 00:44.917
and highly-advanced weaponry.

00:44.959 --> 00:46.750
Yeah, for which side?

00:46.792 --> 00:48.417
Both.

00:49.792 --> 00:51.959
We are approaching

00:49.792 --> 00:51.959
the planet Minos, sir.

00:52.000 --> 00:53.917
Standard orbit, Mr. La Forge.

00:53.959 --> 00:55.709
Aye, sir, standard orbit.

00:55.750 --> 00:58.583
Whatever happened to the<i> Drake</i>

00:55.750 --> 00:58.583
happened quickly.

00:58.625 --> 01:01.709
Otherwise a man like Rice

00:58.625 --> 01:01.709
would have reported again.

01:01.750 --> 01:02.917
You know

01:01.750 --> 01:02.917
Captain Rice?

01:02.959 --> 01:04.792
We were

01:02.959 --> 01:04.792
at the academy together.

01:04.834 --> 01:05.875
Tell me about him.

01:05.917 --> 01:07.000
Able, good officer.

01:07.041 --> 01:09.333
How would he react

01:07.041 --> 01:09.333
under stress?

01:09.375 --> 01:11.834
Paul Rice is confident

01:09.375 --> 01:11.834
to the point of arrogance

01:11.875 --> 01:14.458
but he carries it well

01:11.875 --> 01:14.458
because he's usually right.

01:14.500 --> 01:15.583
He's a risk taker.

01:15.625 --> 01:17.542
Really?

01:15.625 --> 01:17.542
I'll give you an example.

01:17.583 --> 01:20.083
One of the final tests

01:17.583 --> 01:20.083
in Advanced Navigation

01:20.125 --> 01:22.709
at the Academy provides

01:20.125 --> 01:22.709
the students with three options.

01:22.750 --> 01:24.208
Rice was given this test

01:24.250 --> 01:26.542
rejected their options,

01:24.250 --> 01:26.542
and offered one of his own.

01:26.583 --> 01:29.125
That's taking a risk.

01:29.166 --> 01:30.125
And it paid off.

01:30.166 --> 01:31.333
He received the top grade

01:31.375 --> 01:33.125
and now that same test

01:31.375 --> 01:33.125
has four options.

01:33.166 --> 01:34.500
In a difficult situation

01:34.542 --> 01:36.834
a man like that would

01:34.542 --> 01:36.834
act aggressively.

01:36.875 --> 01:37.709
Agreed.

01:37.750 --> 01:38.917
WORF:

01:37.750 --> 01:38.917
Commander.

01:38.959 --> 01:40.333
Weren't you offered

01:38.959 --> 01:40.333
the<i> Drake?</i>

01:40.375 --> 01:41.875
Yes.

01:41.917 --> 01:44.375
You gave up your own command

01:41.917 --> 01:44.375
to take this assignment?

01:44.417 --> 01:46.959
At the time I thought

01:44.417 --> 01:46.959
it would be more advantageous

01:47.000 --> 01:48.917
to do a tour

01:47.000 --> 01:48.917
on the<i> Enterprise.</i>

01:48.959 --> 01:50.458
DATA:

01:48.959 --> 01:50.458
Captain

01:50.500 --> 01:52.583
readings correspond

01:50.500 --> 01:52.583
with the findings of the probe.

01:52.625 --> 01:53.959
No signs

01:52.625 --> 01:53.959
of intelligent life-forms.

01:54.000 --> 01:56.500
Vegetation and

01:54.000 --> 01:56.500
animal life only.

01:56.542 --> 01:58.959
What happened

01:56.542 --> 01:58.959
to all the people?

01:59.000 --> 02:00.458
War?

02:00.500 --> 02:01.875
Disease?

02:01.917 --> 02:03.875
A dissatisfied customer?

02:03.917 --> 02:07.834
In every war, natural disaster,

02:03.917 --> 02:07.834
even the most virulent plague

02:07.875 --> 02:09.750
there are always survivors.

02:09.792 --> 02:10.875
(<i> beeping</i> )

02:10.917 --> 02:12.750
Captain, we are being hailed.

02:12.792 --> 02:15.375
How can that be, from

02:12.792 --> 02:15.375
a planet with no people?

02:15.417 --> 02:18.417
Your sensors indicated

02:15.417 --> 02:18.417
no intelligent life-forms?

02:18.458 --> 02:19.750
Correct, sir.

02:19.792 --> 02:21.542
Something has scanned

02:19.792 --> 02:21.542
our language banks

02:21.583 --> 02:24.125
and is hailing us.

02:24.166 --> 02:26.250
On main viewer.

02:26.291 --> 02:28.667
(<i> beeping</i> )

02:28.709 --> 02:31.375
Whoever you are,

02:28.709 --> 02:31.375
wherever you're from...

02:31.417 --> 02:32.875
greetings.

02:32.917 --> 02:36.208
Welcome to Minos--

02:32.917 --> 02:36.208
the arsenal of freedom.

02:36.250 --> 02:38.250
I'm Captain Jean-Luc Picard

02:36.250 --> 02:38.250
of the<i> U.S.S....</i>

02:38.291 --> 02:39.875
If you need

02:38.291 --> 02:39.875
a little something...

02:39.917 --> 02:44.291
special, be it for one target

02:39.917 --> 02:44.291
or multiple targets

02:44.333 --> 02:45.333
we got it.

02:45.375 --> 02:47.333
You'll see it, here on Minos--

02:47.375 --> 02:49.917
where we live by the motto

02:49.959 --> 02:53.417
"peace through superior

02:49.959 --> 02:53.417
firepower."

02:53.458 --> 02:54.875
To whom am I speaking?

02:54.917 --> 02:58.125
To be totally armed

02:54.917 --> 02:58.125
is to be totally secure.

02:58.166 --> 03:03.125
Remember, the early bird

02:58.166 --> 03:03.125
that hesitates gets wormed.

03:03.166 --> 03:05.083
It is a recorded

03:03.166 --> 03:05.083
message, sir.

03:05.125 --> 03:06.083
Minos--

03:06.125 --> 03:07.792
the arsenal of freedom.

03:07.834 --> 03:10.959
Perfection in highly advanced

03:07.834 --> 03:10.959
weaponry.

03:11.000 --> 03:12.333
Versatility, flexibility...

03:12.375 --> 03:13.875
We must have triggered

03:12.375 --> 03:13.875
something

03:13.917 --> 03:15.208
left over

03:13.917 --> 03:15.208
from the Erselrope Wars

03:15.250 --> 03:16.834
when the arms business

03:15.250 --> 03:16.834
was booming.

03:16.875 --> 03:18.083
...guaranteed.

03:18.125 --> 03:21.333
So lock onto my signal,

03:18.125 --> 03:21.333
and beam on down

03:21.375 --> 03:24.000
because we don't just

03:21.375 --> 03:24.000
provide weapons.

03:24.041 --> 03:24.959
Shut that off.

03:25.000 --> 03:26.000
We provide

03:26.041 --> 03:27.166
complete weapons syst...

03:29.000 --> 03:31.417
That's a heck

03:29.000 --> 03:31.417
of a sales pitch.

03:31.458 --> 03:34.000
If an automatic message system

03:31.458 --> 03:34.000
is still functioning

03:34.041 --> 03:36.000
there could be other systems

03:34.041 --> 03:36.000
on that planet

03:36.041 --> 03:37.125
that are still operational.

03:37.166 --> 03:38.583
Weapons systems?

03:37.166 --> 03:38.583
Possibly.

03:38.625 --> 03:40.125
We're going to have

03:38.625 --> 03:40.125
to go down there to find it.

03:40.166 --> 03:42.000
Number One,

03:40.166 --> 03:42.000
prepare an away team.

03:42.041 --> 03:43.750
Lieutenant Yar,

03:42.041 --> 03:43.750
Data.

03:43.792 --> 03:45.583
Commander, I recommend

03:43.792 --> 03:45.583
a minimum complement.

03:45.625 --> 03:47.041
Oh? I would have

03:45.625 --> 03:47.041
thought otherwise.

03:47.083 --> 03:48.792
We'll keep the first

03:47.083 --> 03:48.792
landing party small

03:48.834 --> 03:51.500
and mobile until I'm confident

03:51.542 --> 03:52.875
whatever killed the inhabitants

03:51.542 --> 03:52.875
of this planet

03:52.917 --> 03:53.917
isn't still down there.

03:53.959 --> 03:55.125
Okay.

04:22.291 --> 04:27.125
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

04:27.166 --> 04:31.250
<i>These are the voyages</i>

04:27.166 --> 04:31.250
<i>of the Starship</i> Enterprise.

04:31.291 --> 04:33.125
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

04:33.166 --> 04:36.542
<i>to explore</i>

04:33.166 --> 04:36.542
<i>strange new worlds</i>

04:36.583 --> 04:41.542
<i>to seek out new life</i>

04:36.583 --> 04:41.542
<i>and new civilizations</i>

04:41.583 --> 04:47.458
<i>to boldly go</i>

04:41.583 --> 04:47.458
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

05:48.333 --> 05:50.250
<i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>

05:50.291 --> 05:54.250
<i>I've ordered an away team</i>

05:50.291 --> 05:54.250
<i>to beam down to Minos</i>

05:54.291 --> 05:57.041
<i>to investigate</i>

05:54.291 --> 05:57.041
<i>the disappearance of the</i> Drake.

05:57.083 --> 06:00.041
<i>Although there are no signs</i>

05:57.083 --> 06:00.041
<i>of intelligent life</i>

06:00.083 --> 06:02.500
<i>coming from this</i>

06:00.083 --> 06:02.500
<i>heavily forested planet</i>

06:02.542 --> 06:05.750
<i>I'm far from certain</i>

06:02.542 --> 06:05.750
<i>that it is devoid of danger.</i>

06:13.583 --> 06:15.417
(<i> beeping</i> )

06:15.458 --> 06:16.750
(<i> bird chirping</i> )

06:16.792 --> 06:19.291
Spooky.

06:19.333 --> 06:20.500
Riker.

06:20.542 --> 06:21.917
This is the Bridge.

06:21.959 --> 06:25.500
We'll start a patterned search

06:21.959 --> 06:25.500
from this point.

06:25.542 --> 06:27.250
Keep this channel open.

06:27.291 --> 06:28.709
Aye, sir.

06:28.750 --> 06:30.417
Commander, our communications

06:28.750 --> 06:30.417
are being monitored.

06:30.458 --> 06:32.125
By whom?

06:32.166 --> 06:37.083
Since there is no intelligent

06:32.166 --> 06:37.083
life, the question is by what?

06:37.125 --> 06:38.208
Captain?

06:38.250 --> 06:40.375
Yes, we heard that,

06:38.250 --> 06:40.375
Number One.

06:40.417 --> 06:43.000
We'll try and track it down

06:40.417 --> 06:43.000
from here.

07:08.000 --> 07:09.583
YAR:

07:08.000 --> 07:09.583
Tritanium.

07:09.625 --> 07:10.583
It's melted.

07:10.625 --> 07:11.792
What could do that?

07:11.834 --> 07:13.583
I don't know, but

07:11.834 --> 07:13.583
whatever it was

07:13.625 --> 07:15.000
it's beyond

07:13.625 --> 07:15.000
our technology.

07:15.041 --> 07:16.667
Over here.

07:21.500 --> 07:24.583
Wow.

07:24.625 --> 07:26.792
We've never seen

07:24.625 --> 07:26.792
anything like this.

07:26.834 --> 07:27.834
It's undamaged.

07:27.875 --> 07:29.375
Maybe a

07:27.875 --> 07:29.375
demonstration model

07:29.417 --> 07:31.083
for some

07:29.417 --> 07:31.083
potential buyer.

07:31.125 --> 07:32.792
Maybe.

07:32.834 --> 07:36.000
Let's spread out

07:32.834 --> 07:36.000
a little.

07:39.041 --> 07:40.291
Commander Riker.

07:40.333 --> 07:41.959
This is Ensign T'su.

07:42.000 --> 07:45.709
I am monitoring a slight energy

07:42.000 --> 07:45.709
buildup near your position.

07:45.750 --> 07:47.792
I'm not able to pinpoint

07:45.750 --> 07:47.792
the source.

07:47.834 --> 07:49.291
Give me a direction.

07:49.333 --> 07:52.375
East of your position,

07:49.333 --> 07:52.375
ten meters.

07:52.417 --> 07:54.834
I will continue monitoring.

07:57.041 --> 07:59.166
I can't see anything

07:57.041 --> 07:59.166
through here.

07:59.208 --> 08:01.875
The underbrush is too thick.

08:06.625 --> 08:08.083
Hello.

08:08.125 --> 08:10.166
Commander Riker.

08:10.208 --> 08:11.709
Rice.

08:13.041 --> 08:15.041
Where did you

08:13.041 --> 08:15.041
come from?

08:15.083 --> 08:17.458
I was over there.

08:17.500 --> 08:18.834
We were worried

08:17.500 --> 08:18.834
about you.

08:18.875 --> 08:20.291
I should have known

08:18.875 --> 08:20.291
you'd pop up.

08:20.333 --> 08:21.709
How are you,

08:20.333 --> 08:21.709
Commander Riker?

08:21.750 --> 08:22.667
Me? Forget about me.

08:22.709 --> 08:23.834
What about you?

08:23.875 --> 08:25.792
No word, no message,

08:23.875 --> 08:25.792
nothing.

08:25.834 --> 08:28.542
How many are with you?

08:25.834 --> 08:28.542
There are two others.

08:28.583 --> 08:31.041
Where's the<i> Drake?</i>

08:28.583 --> 08:31.041
Where's your crew?

08:31.083 --> 08:33.417
PICARD:

08:31.083 --> 08:33.417
Number One, a word.

08:33.458 --> 08:37.458
We have some information

08:33.458 --> 08:37.458
you should be aware of.

08:37.500 --> 08:38.792
Ensign T'su?

08:38.834 --> 08:41.792
Sensors indicate

08:38.834 --> 08:41.792
low-level energy readings

08:41.834 --> 08:44.834
but the only life signs

08:41.834 --> 08:44.834
are the away team.

08:44.875 --> 08:46.500
Do you copy,

08:44.875 --> 08:46.500
Number One?

08:47.667 --> 08:49.041
Understood.

08:56.542 --> 08:58.083
You look strange, Paul.

08:59.709 --> 09:01.458
I was injured getting here.

09:03.000 --> 09:05.583
Do you need

09:03.000 --> 09:05.583
medical help?

09:05.625 --> 09:06.583
No.

09:06.625 --> 09:09.375
What's your purpose here?

09:09.417 --> 09:12.291
Commander Data,

09:09.417 --> 09:12.291
Lieutenant Yar.

09:12.333 --> 09:14.750
Sir, other

09:12.333 --> 09:14.750
than ourselves

09:14.792 --> 09:18.000
I am picking up

09:14.792 --> 09:18.000
no life signs here.

09:18.041 --> 09:20.041
I know.

09:20.083 --> 09:21.750
Riker, you didn't answer me.

09:21.792 --> 09:23.667
Who sent you here

09:21.792 --> 09:23.667
to look for me?

09:23.709 --> 09:24.709
Your mother.

09:24.750 --> 09:27.291
She's worried about you.

09:27.333 --> 09:29.834
Tell me about your ship, Riker.

09:29.875 --> 09:32.625
It's the<i> Enterprise,</i>

09:29.875 --> 09:32.625
isn't it?

09:32.667 --> 09:36.750
No, the name of my ship

09:32.667 --> 09:36.750
is the<i> Lollipop.</i>

09:36.792 --> 09:39.542
I have no knowledge

09:36.792 --> 09:39.542
of that ship.

09:39.583 --> 09:42.083
It's just been commissioned.

09:39.583 --> 09:42.083
It's a good ship.

09:42.125 --> 09:44.208
Refresh me, would you, Riker?

09:44.250 --> 09:46.625
What's its size,

09:44.250 --> 09:46.625
its complement?

09:46.667 --> 09:48.792
Who is here with you?

09:48.834 --> 09:51.250
What's the armament

09:48.834 --> 09:51.250
on the<i> Lollipop?</i>

09:51.291 --> 09:54.166
Paul, I will only answer

09:51.291 --> 09:54.166
your questions

09:54.208 --> 09:55.792
if you answer mine.

09:55.834 --> 09:58.208
Why do you want to know

09:55.834 --> 09:58.208
so much about my ship?

09:58.250 --> 10:00.458
We're friends, aren't we?

10:00.500 --> 10:02.500
Old friends.

10:02.542 --> 10:06.125
Our top speed is warp 3,

10:02.542 --> 10:06.125
what's yours?

10:06.166 --> 10:07.458
"Is"?

10:07.500 --> 10:11.166
Then the<i> Drake</i> has not

10:07.500 --> 10:11.166
been destroyed.

10:11.208 --> 10:12.917
The<i> Drake?</i>

10:12.959 --> 10:14.542
Yes, your ship.

10:14.583 --> 10:17.083
Of course.

10:14.583 --> 10:17.083
My ship is the<i> Drake.</i>

10:17.125 --> 10:18.250
Where is it?

10:18.291 --> 10:19.458
Classified.

10:19.500 --> 10:20.667
Classified?

10:20.709 --> 10:21.667
Please.

10:21.709 --> 10:22.875
It's important.

10:22.917 --> 10:24.667
Our survival depends on knowing.

10:24.709 --> 10:26.875
What's the armament

10:24.709 --> 10:26.875
on your ship?

10:26.917 --> 10:29.041
Ten.

10:26.917 --> 10:29.041
Ten?

10:29.083 --> 10:30.792
I don't understand.

10:29.083 --> 10:30.792
Ten what?

10:30.834 --> 10:33.000
Six.

10:33.041 --> 10:36.166
Commander Riker,

10:33.041 --> 10:36.166
your answers make no sense.

10:36.208 --> 10:38.667
You haven't used

10:36.208 --> 10:38.667
my first name once, Paul.

10:38.709 --> 10:40.333
You remember it, don't you?

10:42.375 --> 10:43.583
You don't, do you?

10:43.625 --> 10:45.417
Because you don't exist.

10:45.458 --> 10:46.792
You're a fake.

10:46.834 --> 10:49.500
You're an image of the original,

10:46.834 --> 10:49.500
aren't you?

10:49.542 --> 10:50.750
Answer me!

10:57.375 --> 10:59.083
PICARD:

10:57.375 --> 10:59.083
Report, Number One.

10:59.125 --> 11:01.208
The image of Rice

10:59.125 --> 11:01.208
has been replaced

11:01.250 --> 11:02.834
by something

11:01.250 --> 11:02.834
which is hovering

11:02.875 --> 11:04.250
several meters away.

11:04.291 --> 11:07.250
Number One,

11:04.291 --> 11:07.250
get your team back up here.

11:07.291 --> 11:09.417
Prepare

11:07.291 --> 11:09.417
to beam up.

11:09.458 --> 11:11.458
(<i> electronic whirring</i> )

11:11.500 --> 11:12.625
Commander!

11:18.709 --> 11:20.083
What's happened, Number One?

11:20.125 --> 11:22.083
Report.

11:22.125 --> 11:24.125
Report, report!

11:24.166 --> 11:25.583
He can't answer you,

11:24.166 --> 11:25.583
Captain.

11:25.625 --> 11:27.333
Commander Riker

11:25.625 --> 11:27.333
has just been encased

11:27.375 --> 11:29.792
in some kind of

11:27.375 --> 11:29.792
energy field.

11:29.834 --> 11:31.959
Is he alive?

11:33.875 --> 11:35.834
Unknown.

11:41.041 --> 11:42.583
<i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>

11:42.625 --> 11:44.750
<i>Some kind of weapon</i>

11:44.792 --> 11:48.291
<i>which, for a time, took</i>

11:44.792 --> 11:48.291
<i>the form of Captain Paul Rice</i>

11:48.333 --> 11:50.959
<i>has enveloped Commander Riker.</i>

11:51.000 --> 11:52.417
Transporter Room 3.

11:52.458 --> 11:54.625
Have you been able to lock on

11:52.458 --> 11:54.625
to the away team?

11:54.667 --> 11:56.834
MAN:

11:54.667 --> 11:56.834
I am unable to lock on

11:54.667 --> 11:56.834
to Commander Riker, sir.

11:56.875 --> 11:58.375
Ensign T'su,

11:56.875 --> 11:58.375
situation report.

