DATA:

12:04.667 --> 12:07.250
He appears to be

12:04.667 --> 12:07.250
in some kind of stasis.

12:07.291 --> 12:08.750
Theorize, Mr. Data.

12:08.792 --> 12:12.083
What would be the purpose

12:08.792 --> 12:12.083
of such an encasement?

12:12.125 --> 12:14.291
Typically, the purpose

12:12.125 --> 12:14.291
of such an enclosure

12:14.333 --> 12:16.125
is for storage.

12:16.166 --> 12:18.041
PICARD:

12:16.166 --> 12:18.041
Which would suggest what?

12:18.083 --> 12:19.583
That sooner or later

12:19.625 --> 12:21.792
someone or something

12:19.625 --> 12:21.792
will be along to collect him.

12:21.834 --> 12:23.208
Stand by.

12:21.834 --> 12:23.208
I'm coming down.

12:23.250 --> 12:24.375
You, sir?

12:24.417 --> 12:26.208
Yes. Dr. Crusher,

12:24.417 --> 12:26.208
this is the Captain.

12:26.250 --> 12:27.959
Meet me in

12:26.250 --> 12:27.959
Transporter Room 3.

12:28.000 --> 12:30.083
Mr. La Forge,

12:28.000 --> 12:30.083
you have command of the Bridge.

12:30.125 --> 12:31.208
Aye, sir.

12:31.250 --> 12:32.709
And whatever

12:31.250 --> 12:32.709
happens down there

12:32.750 --> 12:34.250
your prime

12:32.750 --> 12:34.250
responsibility

12:32.750 --> 12:34.250
is to the ship.

12:34.291 --> 12:35.792
Understood, sir.

12:35.834 --> 12:38.834
Captain, I take exception

12:35.834 --> 12:38.834
