12:38.875 --> 12:40.458
Noted.

12:48.208 --> 12:49.792
Is it just Riker?

12:49.834 --> 12:51.750
Yes. Apparently

12:49.834 --> 12:51.750
he's been confined

12:51.792 --> 12:53.583
inside some sort

12:51.792 --> 12:53.583
of force field.

12:53.625 --> 12:55.000
Energize.

13:04.625 --> 13:05.709
Any changes?

13:05.750 --> 13:07.166
Data's figured

13:05.750 --> 13:07.166
out what it is.

13:07.208 --> 13:09.041
Are you getting

13:07.208 --> 13:09.041
any life signs?

13:09.083 --> 13:10.417
He is alive.

13:10.458 --> 13:12.917
What appeared

13:10.458 --> 13:12.917
in the form of

13:10.458 --> 13:12.917
Captain Rice

13:12.959 --> 13:14.291
is an intelligence-

13:12.959 --> 13:14.291
gathering device

13:14.333 --> 13:15.834
used during the

13:14.333 --> 13:15.834
Erselrope Wars.

13:15.875 --> 13:17.709
Probably developed here.

13:17.750 --> 13:19.000
DATA:

13:17.750 --> 13:19.000
It projects an image

13:19.041 --> 13:20.834
of someone the

13:19.041 --> 13:20.834
subject will trust.

13:20.875 --> 13:22.583
Gets as much information

13:20.875 --> 13:22.583
as possible.

13:22.625 --> 13:25.792
If it's found out,

13:22.625 --> 13:25.792
it encases the subject

13:25.834 --> 13:27.792
to await a more detailed

13:25.834 --> 13:27.792
interrogation later.

13:27.834 --> 13:29.041
Clever.

13:29.083 --> 13:31.166
Can you remove it?

13:29.083 --> 13:31.166
DATA: Possibly.

13:31.208 --> 13:33.542
But I will need to know

13:31.208 --> 13:33.542
the exact frequency

13:33.583 --> 13:35.250
and I cannot

13:33.583 --> 13:35.250
determine the risk

13:35.291 --> 13:36.208
to Commander Riker.

13:36.250 --> 13:37.291
(<i> sighs</i> )

13:37.333 --> 13:39.041
We have little choice.

13:39.083 --> 13:41.583
Whatever has him is interrupting

13:39.083 --> 13:41.583
the transporter beam. Remove it.

13:41.625 --> 13:44.250
(<i> high-pitched beeping</i> )

13:44.291 --> 13:46.250
This will take some time, sir.

13:54.250 --> 13:55.959
(<i> electronic tones</i> )

13:56.000 --> 13:57.500
I am picking up

13:56.000 --> 13:57.500
energy readings.

13:57.542 --> 13:58.917
(<i> beep</i> )

13:58.959 --> 14:01.125
Captain,

13:58.959 --> 14:01.125
Lieutenant La Forge here.

14:01.166 --> 14:04.166
Sensors indicate energy readings

14:01.166 --> 14:04.166
in your area.

14:11.083 --> 14:13.625
Doctor,

14:11.083 --> 14:13.625
over here!

14:23.375 --> 14:24.667
(<i> gasping</i> ):

14:23.375 --> 14:24.667
Oh, no...

14:24.709 --> 14:25.583
Doctor!

14:25.625 --> 14:27.166
(<i> both yell</i> )

14:48.250 --> 14:52.625
(<i> moans softly</i> )

14:52.667 --> 14:54.875
(<i> Picard coughing</i> )

14:56.333 --> 14:59.083
Doctor!

15:03.166 --> 15:06.583
(<i> gasping</i> )

15:11.333 --> 15:13.166
This one is different.

15:16.625 --> 15:18.959
It's anticipating.

15:19.000 --> 15:20.375
Data, I need you.

15:22.250 --> 15:23.875
Set your phaser on kill.

15:23.917 --> 15:25.166
I'll lead left,

15:23.917 --> 15:25.166
you get it.

15:32.458 --> 15:34.000
Captain!

15:35.458 --> 15:37.375
Dr. Crusher?

15:37.417 --> 15:39.959
Captain Picard.

15:40.000 --> 15:41.125
I have a malfunction.

15:41.166 --> 15:42.792
<i>Enterprise,</i> this is Yar.

15:42.834 --> 15:43.917
Mine's out, too.

15:43.959 --> 15:46.041
The close pass

15:43.959 --> 15:46.041
by the weapons

15:46.083 --> 15:47.458
must have disrupted

15:46.083 --> 15:47.458
our communicators.

15:47.500 --> 15:48.709
Keep on working.

15:48.750 --> 15:50.166
I'll look for the Captain

15:48.750 --> 15:50.166
and Dr. Crusher.

15:54.375 --> 15:56.125
Ow, my arm!

15:59.458 --> 16:02.709
How bad is it?

16:02.750 --> 16:03.792
(<i> groans</i> )

16:03.834 --> 16:06.291
It's bad.

16:06.333 --> 16:08.041
(<i> panting</i> )

16:08.083 --> 16:09.041
Hey, come on.

16:09.083 --> 16:11.250
Come on.

16:12.917 --> 16:14.083
All right, d-don't worry.

16:14.125 --> 16:16.166
We'll get you out of here.

16:16.208 --> 16:17.875
<i>Enterprise,</i>

16:16.208 --> 16:17.875
this is the Captain.

16:17.917 --> 16:19.375
Two to beam up.

16:19.417 --> 16:20.625
Oh...<i> </i>

16:19.417 --> 16:20.625
<i>Enterprise!</i>

16:22.834 --> 16:24.250
<i>Enterprise,</i> come in.

16:25.750 --> 16:27.667
Data, Lieutenant Yar.

16:27.709 --> 16:28.792
What's wrong?

16:28.834 --> 16:30.166
Why aren't

16:28.834 --> 16:30.166
they working?

16:30.208 --> 16:31.166
I don't know.

16:31.208 --> 16:32.166
But don't worry.

16:32.208 --> 16:33.959
As soon as they realize

16:34.000 --> 16:36.500
that our communicators

16:34.000 --> 16:36.500
are not working

16:36.542 --> 16:39.667
th-their sensors will find us,

16:36.542 --> 16:39.667
and Geordi will beam us up.

16:40.750 --> 16:43.083
Now, just you hold on.

16:43.125 --> 16:45.125
Uh...

16:45.166 --> 16:46.625
I'm, uh, sorry about this.

16:46.667 --> 16:47.834
(<i> cloth ripping</i> )

16:53.458 --> 16:55.166
Hold on.

16:55.208 --> 16:56.917
It won't be long.

17:01.208 --> 17:05.542
I must keep conscious.

17:09.583 --> 17:11.375
YAR:

17:09.583 --> 17:11.375
Data?

17:11.417 --> 17:13.792
I can't find them.

17:13.834 --> 17:15.083
Step back, please.

17:15.125 --> 17:17.041
I believe I have found it.

17:25.250 --> 17:26.667
Data.

17:28.834 --> 17:31.375
All vital signs

17:28.834 --> 17:31.375
returning to normal.

17:31.417 --> 17:32.500
Good.

17:32.542 --> 17:34.542
Now Geordi can get us

17:32.542 --> 17:34.542
out of here.

17:34.583 --> 17:35.792
Come on.

17:35.834 --> 17:37.375
The Captain

17:35.834 --> 17:37.375
and Dr. Crusher

17:37.417 --> 17:39.291
can't be far away.

17:40.208 --> 17:41.583
(<i> beeping</i> )

17:41.625 --> 17:43.041
Sir, I'm reading

17:41.625 --> 17:43.041
life-forms on

17:41.625 --> 17:43.041
the planet.

17:43.083 --> 17:45.542
All five members

17:43.083 --> 17:45.542
of the away team.

17:45.583 --> 17:47.625
Good. They must have freed

17:45.583 --> 17:47.625
Commander Riker.

17:47.667 --> 17:49.041
Transporter Room

17:49.083 --> 17:51.709
get a lock on the away team,

17:49.083 --> 17:51.709
and beam them up.

17:51.750 --> 17:53.083
Shields just came on.

17:53.125 --> 17:54.792
Deflectors also up.

17:54.834 --> 17:57.750
I'm picking up an object

17:54.834 --> 17:57.750
off the port bow.

17:57.792 --> 17:58.917
It's firing.

18:02.375 --> 18:04.709
Red alert.

18:02.375 --> 18:04.709
Battle stations.

18:04.750 --> 18:07.083
(<i> alarm blaring</i> )

18:09.083 --> 18:10.917
We can't beam the away team up

18:09.083 --> 18:10.917
with our shields in place.

18:10.959 --> 18:12.750
WORF:

18:10.959 --> 18:12.750
Phasers ready.

18:12.792 --> 18:14.333
Photon torpedoes standing by.

18:14.375 --> 18:16.166
Locking on target.

18:16.208 --> 18:17.333
Correction...

18:17.375 --> 18:19.166
target has disappeared.

18:19.208 --> 18:20.208
Give me a full scan.

18:20.250 --> 18:21.375
Scanning.

18:21.417 --> 18:24.000
No readings yet.

18:24.041 --> 18:26.375
Wait. Something dead astern.

18:26.417 --> 18:28.041
Emergency power to shields.

18:28.083 --> 18:29.250
Object is firing.

18:30.291 --> 18:31.417
Return fire.

18:31.458 --> 18:34.000
No use.

18:31.458 --> 18:34.000
It's gone again.

18:34.041 --> 18:35.458
Aft shields weakened.

18:35.500 --> 18:36.834
Whatever they're using

18:36.875 --> 18:39.000
our shields can't stand up to it

18:36.875 --> 18:39.000
much longer.

18:39.041 --> 18:40.375
This is Chief Engineer Logan.

18:40.417 --> 18:43.750
Are we breaking orbit?

18:40.417 --> 18:43.750
I need to know, now!

18:48.792 --> 18:50.875
LA FORGE:

18:48.792 --> 18:50.875
<i>Ship's Log, supplemental.</i>

18:50.917 --> 18:52.417
<i>Lieutenant La Forge in command.</i>

18:52.458 --> 18:54.417
<i>I am unable to beam up</i>

18:52.458 --> 18:54.417
<i>the away team</i>

18:54.458 --> 18:56.208
<i>due to an unseen assailant</i>

18:54.458 --> 18:56.208
<i>attacking the ship.</i>

18:56.250 --> 18:57.792
<i>To make matters worse</i>

18:57.834 --> 19:00.375
<i>Chief Engineer Logan is</i>

18:57.834 --> 19:00.375
<i>on his way to the Bridge</i>

19:00.417 --> 19:02.500
<i>and he's not paying</i>

19:00.417 --> 19:02.500
<i>a courtesy call.</i>

19:04.458 --> 19:05.542
Why are we

19:04.458 --> 19:05.542
still in orbit?

19:05.583 --> 19:06.917
We're taking

19:05.583 --> 19:06.917
a beating.

19:06.959 --> 19:08.709
We've<i> got</i> to hold out

19:06.959 --> 19:08.709
as long as we can.

19:08.750 --> 19:10.375
Now, if can disable

19:08.750 --> 19:10.375
our attacker

19:10.417 --> 19:12.875
if only for a few seconds,

19:10.417 --> 19:12.875
we can drop our shields

19:12.917 --> 19:14.542
and beam the away team

19:12.917 --> 19:14.542
back aboard.

19:14.583 --> 19:17.959
If we follow that plan,

19:14.583 --> 19:17.959
we'll lose the<i> Enterprise.</i>

19:18.000 --> 19:20.208
In view of the

19:18.000 --> 19:20.208
present crisis

19:20.250 --> 19:22.542
I believe you should

19:20.250 --> 19:22.542
relinquish command to me.

19:22.583 --> 19:23.542
No.

19:23.583 --> 19:24.834
I outrank you.

19:24.875 --> 19:27.834
Mr. Logan, I'm in command.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.375
The Captain did not anticipate

19:29.417 --> 19:31.542
the<i> Enterprise</i>

19:29.417 --> 19:31.542
would come under attack.

19:31.583 --> 19:34.417
If he had, would he have

19:31.583 --> 19:34.417
left the Bridge to you?

19:34.458 --> 19:36.667
If he had,

19:34.458 --> 19:36.667
he wouldn't have left the<i> ship!</i>

19:36.709 --> 19:38.500
Picking up an object

19:36.709 --> 19:38.500
to starboard, sir

19:38.542 --> 19:39.500
heading toward us.

19:39.542 --> 19:40.667
Lock phasers

19:39.542 --> 19:40.667
on that thing

19:40.709 --> 19:42.250
and fire the moment

19:40.709 --> 19:42.250
it's in range.

19:42.291 --> 19:44.458
Locking in.

19:44.500 --> 19:45.875
The object has vanished.

19:53.625 --> 19:55.291
Phaser lock lost.

19:55.333 --> 19:57.166
Starboard shields weakened.

19:57.208 --> 19:58.458
It's cloaked itself.

19:58.500 --> 20:00.333
You can't fight this thing

19:58.500 --> 20:00.333
and win.

20:00.375 --> 20:01.917
We've got to break orbit, now!

20:01.959 --> 20:03.583
Worf...

20:03.625 --> 20:06.333
analyze its firing pattern.

20:06.375 --> 20:09.667
Maybe we can anticipate

20:06.375 --> 20:09.667
its location.

20:09.709 --> 20:10.709
Aye.

20:10.750 --> 20:12.000
Solis...

20:12.041 --> 20:13.917
correlate the trajectory

20:12.041 --> 20:13.917
of the energy bolts

20:13.959 --> 20:15.250
with the attack path.

20:15.291 --> 20:17.166
I'll compute

20:15.291 --> 20:17.166
the optimum spread of phaser

20:17.208 --> 20:18.542
and photon torpedoes to hit it.

20:18.583 --> 20:19.625
Right!

20:19.667 --> 20:21.709
Lieutenant

20:19.667 --> 20:21.709
La Forge...

20:21.750 --> 20:24.083
Geordi...

20:24.125 --> 20:26.792
I know you want to do what's

20:24.125 --> 20:26.792
best for the<i> Enterprise.</i>

20:26.834 --> 20:29.333
So do I.

20:26.834 --> 20:29.333
Now, the best thing...

20:29.375 --> 20:32.375
The best thing, Mr. Logan,

20:29.375 --> 20:32.375
is for this discussion to end

20:32.417 --> 20:34.291
and for you to return

20:32.417 --> 20:34.291
to your duties.

20:34.333 --> 20:36.000
Now, I'm in charge

20:34.333 --> 20:36.000
until relieved

20:36.041 --> 20:37.875
by Commander Riker

20:36.041 --> 20:37.875
or Captain Picard.

20:37.917 --> 20:40.333
You're ignoring

20:37.917 --> 20:40.333
my greater rank

20:37.917 --> 20:40.333
and experience.

20:40.375 --> 20:42.000
Not at all.

20:42.041 --> 20:43.250
In fact, just the opposite.

20:43.291 --> 20:44.667
I'm counting on it.

20:44.709 --> 20:46.458
Now, I need you to get

20:44.709 --> 20:46.458
back down to Engineering

20:46.500 --> 20:47.917
and get me every

20:46.500 --> 20:47.917
available scrap

20:47.959 --> 20:49.333
of emergency power you can.

20:49.375 --> 20:50.959
The more power we can

20:49.375 --> 20:50.959
channel to the shields

20:51.000 --> 20:53.417
the longer we'll be able

20:51.000 --> 20:53.417
to hold out.

20:59.583 --> 21:01.458
<i>Now,</i> Mr. Logan.

21:07.083 --> 21:08.417
(<i> sighs</i> )

21:08.458 --> 21:11.500
Worf, have you got

21:08.458 --> 21:11.500
a lock on it yet?

21:11.542 --> 21:14.375
It's impossible

21:11.542 --> 21:14.375
to be sure.

21:21.125 --> 21:22.709
Maybe you should wait here

21:22.750 --> 21:25.834
while Data and I search

21:22.750 --> 21:25.834
for the Captain and Dr. Crusher.

21:25.875 --> 21:27.208
Nah, I'm a

21:25.875 --> 21:27.208
little groggy

21:27.250 --> 21:28.333
but I'll be

21:27.250 --> 21:28.333
all right.

21:28.375 --> 21:30.083
I am getting

21:28.375 --> 21:30.083
energy readings...

21:31.583 --> 21:32.709
Look out!

21:40.667 --> 21:44.041
We'll do it

21:40.667 --> 21:44.041
just like before.

21:55.208 --> 21:56.875
It's got a deflector shield.

21:56.917 --> 21:59.709
The product continues

21:56.917 --> 21:59.709
to upgrade and improve.

21:59.750 --> 22:02.375
We'll concentrate our fire

21:59.750 --> 22:02.375
and try to collapse its shield.

22:02.417 --> 22:05.125
Commander,

22:02.417 --> 22:05.125
we'll need you, too.

22:08.875 --> 22:09.959
Now!

22:23.250 --> 22:25.834
You're right.

22:23.250 --> 22:25.834
They keep on getting better.

22:25.875 --> 22:27.375
The weapons

22:25.875 --> 22:27.375
are appearing

22:27.417 --> 22:30.000
at intervals of

22:27.417 --> 22:30.000
precisely 12 minutes.

22:30.041 --> 22:32.417
Well, this one took

22:30.041 --> 22:32.417
everything we had.

22:32.458 --> 22:34.208
I don't know how

22:32.458 --> 22:34.208
we'll handle the next one.

22:34.250 --> 22:35.792
We're not going

22:34.250 --> 22:35.792
to wait around.

22:35.834 --> 22:37.542
Let's find

22:35.834 --> 22:37.542
the rest of our team.

22:43.250 --> 22:47.959
(<i> water dripping</i> )

22:48.000 --> 22:53.208
We seem to be in some kind

22:48.000 --> 22:53.208
of underground structure.

22:53.250 --> 22:55.709
but I don't see any...

22:55.750 --> 22:58.458
Hey.

22:58.500 --> 22:59.750
No, you don't.

22:59.792 --> 23:01.333
No time to sleep.

23:01.375 --> 23:02.291
I'm tired.

23:02.333 --> 23:03.417
Come on,

23:02.333 --> 23:03.417
stay with me.

23:03.458 --> 23:05.125
Come on, now,

23:03.458 --> 23:05.125
stay awake.

23:05.166 --> 23:06.542
That's an order.

23:06.583 --> 23:09.375
I must have lost

23:06.583 --> 23:09.375
a lot of blood.

23:10.625 --> 23:13.291
I stopped the bleeding.

23:13.333 --> 23:16.291
No, there's

23:13.333 --> 23:16.291
another wound.

23:16.333 --> 23:17.709
My leg.

23:21.500 --> 23:24.291
(<i> cry of pain</i> )

23:25.959 --> 23:27.500
Ah, not to worry.

23:27.542 --> 23:30.792
Everything's going

23:27.542 --> 23:30.792
to be fine.

23:30.834 --> 23:34.458
Now... this is going

23:30.834 --> 23:34.458
to hurt a bit.

23:34.500 --> 23:37.792
I've heard that before.

23:37.834 --> 23:39.125
(<i> moaning</i> )

23:44.834 --> 23:48.583
Hey, hey, Doctor,

23:44.834 --> 23:48.583
stay awake, come on.

23:48.625 --> 23:49.667
There's a lot of blood.

23:49.709 --> 23:50.750
What do I do next?

23:50.792 --> 23:52.458
Doctor.

23:52.500 --> 23:57.625
Uh... the wound needs

23:52.500 --> 23:57.625
a clotting agent.

23:57.667 --> 23:59.792
I couldn't find

23:57.667 --> 23:59.792
your medical kit.

24:02.125 --> 24:04.333
Those roots... what are they?

24:04.375 --> 24:05.333
Roots?

24:05.375 --> 24:07.291
What, these?

24:09.041 --> 24:11.208
Break off a piece

24:09.041 --> 24:11.208
and taste it.

24:11.250 --> 24:12.750
Don't swallow it.

24:22.500 --> 24:23.709
Very bitter.

24:23.750 --> 24:26.583
Apply some to your hand.

24:27.625 --> 24:30.625
Is there

24:27.625 --> 24:30.625
a color change?

24:30.667 --> 24:32.583
It's-It's turning yellowish.

24:32.625 --> 24:38.208
Good. Now, spread as much of it

24:32.625 --> 24:38.208
as you can onto the wound.

24:46.375 --> 24:47.417
Hey, hey, Doctor!

24:47.458 --> 24:48.542
Now, stay awake.

24:48.583 --> 24:49.834
(<i> pounding root</i> )

24:49.875 --> 24:51.417
You've got

24:49.875 --> 24:51.417
to help me.

24:51.458 --> 24:55.000
I need your help.

24:57.500 --> 24:58.709
All right, now listen.

24:58.750 --> 25:00.333
Your patient

25:00.375 --> 25:05.583
has lost a great deal of blood

25:00.375 --> 25:05.583
from multiple lacerations.

25:07.291 --> 25:09.583
The patient's going into shock.

25:09.625 --> 25:11.667
So what do I do?

25:11.709 --> 25:16.667
Elevate the legs,

25:11.709 --> 25:16.667
and try to keep her warm.

25:19.166 --> 25:20.166
Good.

25:20.208 --> 25:21.917
All right?

25:21.959 --> 25:23.208
(<i> groans in pain</i> )

25:23.250 --> 25:24.333
Stay with me, Doctor.

25:26.834 --> 25:29.083
Keep talking.

25:33.291 --> 25:36.166
Well... you didn't happen

25:36.208 --> 25:37.834
to bring a blanket

25:36.208 --> 25:37.834
with you, did you?

25:37.875 --> 25:40.208
No.

25:41.625 --> 25:43.291
I'm going to look

25:41.625 --> 25:43.291
for a way out.

25:45.625 --> 25:47.834
Now, you keep up your end.

25:47.875 --> 25:50.375
Stay awake.

26:07.000 --> 26:09.291
LA FORGE:

26:07.000 --> 26:09.291
All right

26:09.333 --> 26:11.542
I know it's risky

26:11.583 --> 26:14.417
but a shot in the dark

26:11.583 --> 26:14.417
is better than nothing.

26:14.458 --> 26:17.750
Let's see

26:14.458 --> 26:17.750
if we can get lucky.

26:17.792 --> 26:21.709
I can't seem

26:17.792 --> 26:21.709
to pin down

26:17.792 --> 26:21.709
the pattern.

26:22.875 --> 26:23.959
(<i> beeping</i> )

26:24.000 --> 26:24.917
There.

26:24.959 --> 26:25.917
Sorry, sir.

26:25.959 --> 26:27.000
I should have

26:25.959 --> 26:27.000
seen that.

26:27.041 --> 26:28.000
No, that's all right.

26:28.041 --> 26:29.000
You're doing fine.

26:29.041 --> 26:30.208
WORF:

26:29.041 --> 26:30.208
Program laid in.

26:30.250 --> 26:32.250
Phasers and photon torpedoes

26:30.250 --> 26:32.250
ready.

26:32.291 --> 26:34.750
Okay.

26:34.792 --> 26:40.542
Mr. Solis, bring her about

26:34.792 --> 26:40.542
to 23, mark 185.

26:40.583 --> 26:42.875
Aye, sir.

26:47.917 --> 26:49.417
Fire!

26:49.458 --> 26:50.583
Now!

26:50.625 --> 26:51.959
Phasers and photons firing.

26:57.834 --> 26:59.959
We<i> missed!</i>

27:00.000 --> 27:01.375
Number 4 shield

27:00.000 --> 27:01.375
buckling.

27:03.625 --> 27:05.166
Number 3 shield nearing failure.

27:05.208 --> 27:06.834
LOGAN:

27:05.208 --> 27:06.834
Bridge, this is Engineering.

27:06.875 --> 27:08.917
I can't hold this power level

27:06.875 --> 27:08.917
much longer.

27:08.959 --> 27:10.542
You've got to<i> do</i> something!

27:10.583 --> 27:12.500
Backup systems

27:10.583 --> 27:12.500
are overloaded.

27:12.542 --> 27:14.458
Backup systems failing!

27:14.500 --> 27:15.917
LOGAN:

27:14.500 --> 27:15.917
La Forge!

27:15.959 --> 27:17.959
This is Logan.

27:18.000 --> 27:19.417
Tell me something.

27:23.458 --> 27:27.458
Mr. Logan, report to the Bridge.

27:33.250 --> 27:35.291
On my way.

27:46.667 --> 27:48.041
Deflectors are

27:46.667 --> 27:48.041
breaking down.

27:48.083 --> 27:51.083
We have less than

27:48.083 --> 27:51.083
one minute of reserve.

27:51.125 --> 27:53.583
We're getting

27:51.125 --> 27:53.583
out of here.

27:53.625 --> 27:58.125
Lieutenant Solis,

27:53.625 --> 27:58.125
set course 315,

27:53.625 --> 27:58.125
mark 007.

27:58.166 --> 28:00.125
Course set.

28:00.166 --> 28:01.583
You are leaving them

28:00.166 --> 28:01.583
on the planet.

28:01.625 --> 28:02.875
Speed, warp 5.

28:02.917 --> 28:05.166
Warp 5. Aye.

28:15.500 --> 28:17.208
Engage.

28:28.667 --> 28:32.166
Hold course and speed

28:28.667 --> 28:32.166
for 28 seconds

28:32.208 --> 28:34.583
then come to a full stop.

28:34.625 --> 28:36.917
Mr. Logan...

28:36.959 --> 28:39.250
had we stayed,

28:36.959 --> 28:39.250
we would have been destroyed

28:39.291 --> 28:41.000
and there are over

28:39.291 --> 28:41.000
a thousand people on this ship.

28:41.041 --> 28:42.583
I have a responsibility

28:41.041 --> 28:42.583
to them.

28:42.625 --> 28:44.041
What about your

28:42.625 --> 28:44.041
responsibility

28:44.083 --> 28:45.125
to Captain Picard

28:44.083 --> 28:45.125
and the members

28:45.166 --> 28:46.417
of the away team?

28:46.458 --> 28:49.875
I have a responsibility

28:46.458 --> 28:49.875
to them, as well.

28:49.917 --> 28:53.834
Mr. Logan, you are going

28:49.917 --> 28:53.834
to take command...

28:54.917 --> 28:57.083
...of the Saucer Section.

28:57.125 --> 28:59.917
Back up crew,

28:57.125 --> 28:59.917
report to the Main Bridge.

28:59.959 --> 29:01.250
We're going to separate?

29:01.291 --> 29:03.125
Yes, and I want you

29:01.291 --> 29:03.125
to take the Saucer Section

29:03.166 --> 29:04.875
and proceed immediately

29:03.166 --> 29:04.875
to Starbase 103.

29:04.917 --> 29:07.166
You can't fight

29:04.917 --> 29:07.166
what you can't see.

29:07.208 --> 29:09.500
And you still won't be

29:07.208 --> 29:09.500
able to see that thing.

29:09.542 --> 29:10.834
Maybe we won't have to.

29:10.875 --> 29:12.041
Risky.

29:12.083 --> 29:15.166
Yes. That's why

29:12.083 --> 29:15.166
we're going to separate.

29:15.208 --> 29:17.333
Worf, Solis, T'su...

29:17.375 --> 29:18.834
report to the Battle Bridge.

29:18.875 --> 29:20.125
I'll join you in a moment.

29:20.166 --> 29:21.834
WORF:

29:20.166 --> 29:21.834
Ensign, secure

29:20.166 --> 29:21.834
connector levels.

29:21.875 --> 29:24.083
MAN:

29:21.875 --> 29:24.083
Aye, sir.

29:44.166 --> 29:46.208
(<i> door chimes</i> )

29:46.250 --> 29:47.583
Come in.

29:51.542 --> 29:55.250
Lieutenant, I need

29:51.542 --> 29:55.250
to speak to you.

29:55.291 --> 29:56.750
Counselor,

29:55.291 --> 29:56.750
we're a few minutes away

29:56.792 --> 29:58.333
from separating

29:56.792 --> 29:58.333
the battle section.

29:58.375 --> 29:59.333
I don't have a lot of time.

29:59.375 --> 30:01.125
I know,

29:59.375 --> 30:01.125
but as counselor

30:01.166 --> 30:03.041
I have a duty

30:01.166 --> 30:03.041
to evaluate

30:03.083 --> 30:05.500
the emotional

30:03.083 --> 30:05.500
fitness of the crew.

30:05.542 --> 30:10.000
And you sense I'm nervous?

30:10.041 --> 30:11.417
Well, you're right.

30:11.458 --> 30:15.333
Counselor, deep down,

30:11.458 --> 30:15.333
I'm shaking.

30:15.375 --> 30:17.166
I'm about to take

30:15.375 --> 30:17.166
this ship into battle

30:17.208 --> 30:18.500
and-and there's a good chance

30:18.542 --> 30:20.250
she'll be blasted

30:18.542 --> 30:20.250
out of the sky.

30:20.291 --> 30:21.917
I'm taking

30:20.291 --> 30:21.917
a huge risk here

30:21.959 --> 30:24.291
and there are

30:21.959 --> 30:24.291
a lot of lives at stake.

30:24.333 --> 30:27.291
So, yeah, I'm nervous.

30:27.333 --> 30:28.792
Did you expect otherwise?

30:28.834 --> 30:29.917
Not at all.

30:29.959 --> 30:31.500
You're under

30:29.959 --> 30:31.500
tremendous pressure

30:31.542 --> 30:33.291
more than you've

30:31.542 --> 30:33.291
ever experienced.

30:33.333 --> 30:35.083
And you think

30:33.333 --> 30:35.083
I'm about to crack?

30:35.125 --> 30:37.250
On the contrary,

30:35.125 --> 30:37.250
you should be proud

30:37.291 --> 30:39.166
of the way

30:37.291 --> 30:39.166
you're handling command.

30:39.208 --> 30:42.333
You've kept a cool

30:39.208 --> 30:42.333
head, taken charge

30:42.375 --> 30:44.792
and made some very

30:42.375 --> 30:44.792
difficult decisions.

30:44.834 --> 30:46.291
Then what did you want

30:44.834 --> 30:46.291
to see me about?

30:46.333 --> 30:48.083
SOLIS:

30:46.333 --> 30:48.083
Lieutenant La Forge

30:48.125 --> 30:50.375
Battle Bridge

30:48.125 --> 30:50.375
is manned and ready.

30:50.417 --> 30:53.542
However, deflectors have not yet

30:50.417 --> 30:53.542
returned to full efficiency.

30:53.583 --> 30:56.208
Let's get them there,

30:53.583 --> 30:56.208
Mr. Solis.

30:56.250 --> 30:57.417
Aye, sir.

30:57.458 --> 30:58.542
I'll join you shortly.

30:58.583 --> 30:59.959
La Forge out.

31:00.000 --> 31:03.583
Did you hear the

31:00.000 --> 31:03.583
uneasiness in his voice?

31:03.625 --> 31:05.792
Solis is doing a fine job.

31:05.834 --> 31:07.458
Yes, but he isn't

31:05.834 --> 31:07.458
handling the stress

31:07.500 --> 31:08.792
as well as you are.

31:08.834 --> 31:10.750
Both he and Ensign T'su

31:08.834 --> 31:10.750
are very young.

31:10.792 --> 31:12.583
No, wait.

31:10.792 --> 31:12.583
They're good officers.

31:12.625 --> 31:15.125
Yes, but they lack

31:12.625 --> 31:15.125
battle experience.

31:15.166 --> 31:17.291
They're worried

31:15.166 --> 31:17.291
about making mistakes

31:17.333 --> 31:19.417
and they need

31:17.333 --> 31:19.417
some encouragement.

31:19.458 --> 31:21.917
What do I do?

31:21.959 --> 31:26.583
Just remember, it's<i> you</i>

31:21.959 --> 31:26.583
they draw strength from.

31:26.625 --> 31:30.250
They look to you

31:26.625 --> 31:30.250
for guidance and

31:26.625 --> 31:30.250
for leadership.

31:33.208 --> 31:35.625
Help them.

31:35.667 --> 31:38.625
Show confidence in them.

31:38.667 --> 31:42.709
Like Captain Picard

31:38.667 --> 31:42.709
showed confidence in me.

31:42.750 --> 31:43.875
Right.

31:43.917 --> 31:45.333
(<i> sighing</i> )

31:45.375 --> 31:46.458
I understand.

31:46.500 --> 31:48.375
Thanks, Counselor.

32:01.500 --> 32:04.208
Prepare to initiate

32:01.500 --> 32:04.208
separation sequence.

32:04.250 --> 32:06.333
All decks

32:04.250 --> 32:06.333
report ready.

32:06.375 --> 32:08.125
On my mark.

32:16.250 --> 32:17.375
Now.

32:30.417 --> 32:33.458
COMPUTER:

32:30.417 --> 32:33.458
Main-latch mags to zero.

32:33.500 --> 32:36.917
Main-latch retraction, 1 to 18.

32:36.959 --> 32:37.959
Initiate.

32:38.000 --> 32:41.000
Static charge, compensated.

32:48.041 --> 32:49.625
Separation complete.

32:49.667 --> 32:50.917
Lieutenant Solis

32:50.959 --> 32:54.500
lay in a reciprocal course

32:50.959 --> 32:54.500
for Minos, warp 5.

32:54.542 --> 32:55.583
Course set.

32:55.625 --> 32:58.166
On my mark.

32:58.208 --> 33:00.250
Engage.

33:12.208 --> 33:16.166
We seem to be pretty well

33:12.208 --> 33:16.166
sealed in, Doctor.

33:16.208 --> 33:18.083
No exits?

33:18.125 --> 33:19.834
None that

33:18.125 --> 33:19.834
I can see.

33:19.875 --> 33:22.917
If you find one, go.

33:22.959 --> 33:27.000
Uh-huh, tired

33:22.959 --> 33:27.000
of my company already?

33:27.041 --> 33:29.208
Beverly?

33:29.250 --> 33:30.792
Beverly?!

33:30.834 --> 33:34.291
I'm tired.

33:30.834 --> 33:34.291
I need to sleep.

33:34.333 --> 33:36.792
Woke up too early.

33:36.834 --> 33:37.917
Talk to me.

33:36.834 --> 33:37.917
Stay awake.

33:37.959 --> 33:39.834
Tell me something.

33:39.875 --> 33:42.041
Tell me about, uh...

33:39.875 --> 33:42.041
about those roots.

33:42.083 --> 33:44.834
How did you know

33:42.083 --> 33:44.834
their medicinal values?

33:44.875 --> 33:46.417
My grandmother.

33:46.458 --> 33:48.709
Your grandmother was a doctor?

33:48.750 --> 33:50.291
No.

33:50.333 --> 33:52.000
Oh, she was a

33:50.333 --> 33:52.000
botanist then?

33:52.041 --> 33:54.959
Uh... no.

33:55.000 --> 33:58.000
She helped to colonize

33:55.000 --> 33:58.000
Arvada III.

33:58.041 --> 34:01.458
Arvada III?

34:01.500 --> 34:04.583
That's such a tragedy.

34:01.500 --> 34:04.583
Did she survive?

34:04.625 --> 34:07.250
Yes.

34:07.291 --> 34:10.792
Once the medical supplies

34:07.291 --> 34:10.792
had run out

34:10.834 --> 34:13.709
she had to use what was at hand.

34:13.750 --> 34:17.417
So she learned

34:13.750 --> 34:17.417
all about roots and herbs

34:17.458 --> 34:20.083
and then

34:17.458 --> 34:20.083
taught it to me.

34:20.125 --> 34:23.125
You were part of that colony.

34:20.125 --> 34:23.125
I didn't know that.

34:23.166 --> 34:26.250
But then there must be

34:23.166 --> 34:26.250
a lot of things about you

34:26.291 --> 34:27.291
that I don't know.

34:27.333 --> 34:30.417
Quite a few.

34:30.458 --> 34:31.792
What?

34:31.834 --> 34:35.166
Now, just a minute,

34:31.834 --> 34:35.166
here's something odd.

34:35.208 --> 34:37.333
It's glowing.

34:37.375 --> 34:38.291
What is it?

34:38.333 --> 34:39.750
I don't know.

34:39.792 --> 34:41.250
It's... it's covered up.

34:41.291 --> 34:45.125
Just... just clearing away

34:41.291 --> 34:45.125
the dirt.

34:45.166 --> 34:48.166
It's a viewscreen.

34:51.417 --> 34:56.333
It seems to

34:51.417 --> 34:56.333
still be

34:51.417 --> 34:56.333
operative.

35:01.917 --> 35:04.291
(<i> buzzing, beeps</i> )

35:04.333 --> 35:08.291
(<i> startup whirring</i> )

35:08.333 --> 35:09.834
(<i> electronic humming</i> )

35:09.875 --> 35:12.250
It's a tracking device

35:09.875 --> 35:12.250
of some kind.

35:12.291 --> 35:14.125
Tracking what?

35:14.166 --> 35:17.208
There are three

35:14.166 --> 35:17.208
moving indicators.

35:17.250 --> 35:19.208
Possibly the away team.

35:24.583 --> 35:25.959
Beautiful, isn't it?

35:26.000 --> 35:28.625
It's the centerpiece

35:26.000 --> 35:28.625
of the whole unit.

35:28.667 --> 35:30.667
Who's that?

35:33.000 --> 35:34.542
A projection.

35:34.583 --> 35:36.083
It's the automated

35:34.583 --> 35:36.083
salesman

35:36.125 --> 35:38.250
who greeted us

35:36.125 --> 35:38.250
on the<i> Enterprise.</i>

35:38.291 --> 35:39.458
What unit?

35:39.500 --> 35:41.750
Why, the Echo Papa 607--

35:41.792 --> 35:43.875
our proudest achievement.

35:43.917 --> 35:46.959
The ultimate

35:43.917 --> 35:46.959
in weapons system technology.

35:47.000 --> 35:50.166
Is that what's behind

35:47.000 --> 35:50.166
the attack on my people?

35:50.208 --> 35:53.125
Impressive demonstration,

35:50.208 --> 35:53.125
isn't it?

35:53.166 --> 35:55.709
Demonstration?

35:53.166 --> 35:55.709
It tried to kill us.

35:55.750 --> 35:58.458
Versatile, powerful,

35:55.750 --> 35:58.458
and easy to use.

35:58.500 --> 36:00.083
The 607

35:58.500 --> 36:00.083
does it all.

36:00.125 --> 36:02.333
Its various modules

36:02.375 --> 36:06.250
can gather information,

36:02.375 --> 36:06.250
neutralize ground personnel

36:06.291 --> 36:09.083
even destroy

36:06.291 --> 36:09.083
enemy space vessels.

36:09.125 --> 36:12.291
The<i> Enterprise.</i>

36:12.333 --> 36:14.583
Is one of those things

36:12.333 --> 36:14.583
after my ship?

36:14.625 --> 36:15.792
Tell me.

36:15.834 --> 36:17.166
Of course I can tell you.

36:17.208 --> 36:19.959
I am programmed to answer

36:17.208 --> 36:19.959
any and all questions

36:20.000 --> 36:21.166
about the unit.

36:21.208 --> 36:23.458
I can talk terms,

36:21.208 --> 36:23.458
arrange for delivery--

36:23.500 --> 36:25.166
whatever you need.

36:25.208 --> 36:29.083
It doesn't understand anything

36:25.208 --> 36:29.083
other than what it's peddling.

36:29.125 --> 36:31.834
The 607 represents

36:29.125 --> 36:31.834
the state of the art

36:31.875 --> 36:33.917
in dynamic adaptive design.

36:33.959 --> 36:37.834
It learns from each encounter

36:33.959 --> 36:37.834
and improves itself.

36:37.875 --> 36:40.083
So what went wrong?

36:37.875 --> 36:40.083
Where are its creators?

36:40.125 --> 36:41.667
Where are the people of Minos?

36:41.709 --> 36:44.875
Once unleashed,

36:41.709 --> 36:44.875
the unit is invincible.

36:44.917 --> 36:47.291
The perfect killing system.

36:47.333 --> 36:50.875
Too perfect.

36:50.917 --> 36:54.917
You poor fools,

36:50.917 --> 36:54.917
your own creation destroyed you.

36:54.959 --> 36:56.750
(<i> electronic whooshing</i> )

36:56.792 --> 36:58.333
What was that noise?

36:58.375 --> 37:01.000
The unit has analyzed

36:58.375 --> 37:01.000
its last attack

37:01.041 --> 37:03.834
and constructed

37:01.041 --> 37:03.834
a new, stronger...

37:03.875 --> 37:05.291
deadlier weapon.

37:05.333 --> 37:07.583
In a moment,

37:05.333 --> 37:07.583
it will launch that weapon

37:07.625 --> 37:10.291
against the targets

37:07.625 --> 37:10.291
on the surface.

37:10.333 --> 37:11.667
Abort it!

37:11.709 --> 37:13.291
Why would I want to do that?

37:13.333 --> 37:15.917
It can't demonstrate

37:13.333 --> 37:15.917
its abilities

37:15.959 --> 37:19.083
unless we let it

37:15.959 --> 37:19.083
leave the nest.

37:21.083 --> 37:22.959
They are down there, sir.

37:23.000 --> 37:24.583
Let's clear

37:23.000 --> 37:24.583
some of that away.

37:24.625 --> 37:26.250
If Data's

37:24.625 --> 37:26.250
calculations

37:24.625 --> 37:26.250
are correct

37:26.291 --> 37:28.125
the next one

37:26.291 --> 37:28.125
should show itself

37:28.166 --> 37:30.166
in two minutes.

37:32.250 --> 37:33.417
Captain!

37:33.458 --> 37:34.709
Can you hear me?

37:34.750 --> 37:36.583
Yes, we're here!

37:36.625 --> 37:38.250
Are you all right?

37:39.792 --> 37:41.834
Dr. Crusher is seriously hurt.

37:41.875 --> 37:43.875
We can't contact

37:41.875 --> 37:43.875
the<i> Enterprise.</i>

37:43.917 --> 37:45.458
The communicators are out.

37:45.500 --> 37:47.500
Yes, our communicators

37:45.500 --> 37:47.500
are out, too.

37:47.542 --> 37:48.792
Those devices

37:48.834 --> 37:51.083
are part of a system

37:48.834 --> 37:51.083
located down here.

37:51.125 --> 37:53.583
Another one is about

37:51.125 --> 37:53.583
to be released.

37:51.125 --> 37:53.583
Watch yourself!

37:53.625 --> 37:55.125
We know, Captain.

37:55.166 --> 37:56.291
It's too far down there.

37:56.333 --> 37:57.542
There's nothing

37:56.333 --> 37:57.542
to hold on to.

37:57.583 --> 37:58.834
There's no way

37:57.583 --> 37:58.834
to climb down.

37:58.875 --> 38:00.458
I'm surprised either

37:58.875 --> 38:00.458
of them survived.

38:00.500 --> 38:01.500
I can do it,

38:00.500 --> 38:01.500
Commander.

38:01.542 --> 38:02.625
How?

38:02.667 --> 38:04.667
Jump.

38:04.709 --> 38:07.083
Data, it's over ten meters.

38:07.125 --> 38:09.000
11.75, sir.

38:09.041 --> 38:10.500
Data...

38:10.542 --> 38:12.959
you may be sturdy,

38:10.542 --> 38:12.959
but you're not indestructible.

38:13.000 --> 38:16.333
I believe I can safely

38:13.000 --> 38:16.333
traverse the distance.

38:16.375 --> 38:19.458
Captain, Data is going

38:19.500 --> 38:21.750
to join you down there.

38:23.709 --> 38:25.083
Be my guest.

38:30.458 --> 38:32.041
Data.

38:32.083 --> 38:34.083
At your service, Captain.

38:43.500 --> 38:45.500
We'd better find

38:43.500 --> 38:45.500
a defensive position.

38:45.542 --> 38:46.625
If Data's right...

38:46.667 --> 38:48.125
He usually is.

38:48.166 --> 38:50.458
We're going to have company

38:48.166 --> 38:50.458
any minute now

38:50.500 --> 38:53.542
and this time, I don't know

38:50.500 --> 38:53.542
how we're going to stop it.

38:55.417 --> 38:57.417
LA FORGE:

38:55.417 --> 38:57.417
<i>Ship's Log, supplemental.</i>

38:57.458 --> 39:00.792
<i>Lieutenant La Forge in command</i>

38:57.458 --> 39:00.792
<i>of the stardrive section.</i>

39:00.834 --> 39:02.750
<i>After separating</i>

39:00.834 --> 39:02.750
<i>from the saucer</i>

39:02.792 --> 39:05.750
<i>we have returned to Minos</i>

39:02.792 --> 39:05.750
<i>to rescue the away team.</i>

39:05.792 --> 39:09.291
<i>Unfortunately, I have</i>

39:05.792 --> 39:09.291
<i>only one option left</i>

39:09.333 --> 39:11.083
<i>and it's a long shot.</i>

39:11.125 --> 39:14.125
Shields and

39:11.125 --> 39:14.125
deflectors are up.

39:14.166 --> 39:16.750
Ensign T'su,

39:14.166 --> 39:16.750
when I order the shields down

39:16.792 --> 39:18.166
you have one responsibility:

39:18.208 --> 39:20.917
locate the away team,

39:18.208 --> 39:20.917
and get them up here.

39:20.959 --> 39:22.792
You may only have a few seconds.

39:22.834 --> 39:24.750
Approaching

39:22.834 --> 39:24.750
the planet, sir.

39:24.792 --> 39:27.250
Ride's going to get

39:24.792 --> 39:27.250
a little bumpy.

39:27.291 --> 39:28.667
Things are going to happen fast.

39:28.709 --> 39:32.875
Just keep alert,

39:28.709 --> 39:32.875
stay calm.

39:32.917 --> 39:34.625
Let's focus on what we're doing.

39:34.667 --> 39:36.959
You know your jobs.

39:37.000 --> 39:39.375
You've been trained,

39:37.000 --> 39:39.375
you've been tested...

39:39.417 --> 39:42.166
and you've earned the right

39:39.417 --> 39:42.166
to sit in those chairs.

39:44.667 --> 39:46.709
(<i> rhythmic beeping</i> )

39:49.709 --> 39:50.875
(<i> electronic whooshing</i> )

39:50.917 --> 39:52.792
That sound again.

39:52.834 --> 39:54.417
Another weapon has

39:52.834 --> 39:54.417
been launched, sir.

39:54.458 --> 39:56.375
We've got to find some way

39:54.458 --> 39:56.375
to stop the system.

39:56.417 --> 39:58.417
I would need to see

39:56.417 --> 39:58.417
the program's schematic.

39:58.458 --> 39:59.583
You've got it.

39:59.625 --> 40:01.083
(<i> beeping whine</i> )

40:01.125 --> 40:03.125
Is it possible

40:01.125 --> 40:03.125
to readjust

40:03.166 --> 40:05.166
the targeting

40:03.166 --> 40:05.166
sequence?

40:05.208 --> 40:06.375
Absolutely.

40:06.417 --> 40:08.166
It wouldn't be much good

40:06.417 --> 40:08.166
without it.

40:08.208 --> 40:09.500
Data, assign it

40:08.208 --> 40:09.500
a neutral target.

40:09.542 --> 40:10.917
Target must be

40:09.542 --> 40:10.917
specific, sir.

40:10.959 --> 40:12.667
Itself, then. Itself

40:10.959 --> 40:12.667
or its own power source.

40:12.709 --> 40:13.792
The force of

40:12.709 --> 40:13.792
that explosion

40:13.834 --> 40:14.959
would destroy

40:13.834 --> 40:14.959
this cavern

40:15.000 --> 40:16.208
and everyone

40:15.000 --> 40:16.208
on the surface.

40:16.250 --> 40:17.542
Watch now.

40:17.583 --> 40:21.583
This is the fourth

40:17.583 --> 40:21.583
and final projectile.

40:21.625 --> 40:24.458
The Echo Papa Series 607

40:24.500 --> 40:28.083
is about to complete

40:24.500 --> 40:28.083
this phase of its mission.

40:28.125 --> 40:29.083
We could split up.

40:29.125 --> 40:30.125
What good would that do?

40:30.166 --> 40:31.542
Confuse it, delay it,

40:30.166 --> 40:31.542
something.

40:31.583 --> 40:32.792
It would still get us.

40:32.834 --> 40:34.291
It would just take

40:32.834 --> 40:34.291
a little longer.

40:34.333 --> 40:36.125
It might give one of us time

40:34.333 --> 40:36.125
to get out of range.

40:36.166 --> 40:37.083
Out of range?

40:37.125 --> 40:38.166
(<i> sighs</i> )

40:38.208 --> 40:39.667
Forget I said it.

40:39.709 --> 40:41.250
These devices wiped out

40:39.709 --> 40:41.250
an entire planet.

40:41.291 --> 40:42.417
I don't think

40:41.291 --> 40:42.417
it has a range.

40:42.458 --> 40:43.875
Then what does

40:42.458 --> 40:43.875
that leave us?

40:43.917 --> 40:46.083
(<i> sighs</i> )

40:46.125 --> 40:48.041
Right. That's

40:46.125 --> 40:48.041
what I thought.

40:48.083 --> 40:50.125
On the other hand,

40:48.083 --> 40:50.125
we could look

40:50.166 --> 40:51.250
for different cover!

40:56.291 --> 40:59.333
(<i> electronic whirring</i> )

40:59.375 --> 41:01.291
You got any ideas?

41:01.333 --> 41:02.959
None.

41:05.417 --> 41:08.250
Give me some options,

41:05.417 --> 41:08.250
Data, quickly.

41:08.291 --> 41:10.166
Why don't you just shut it off?

41:10.208 --> 41:12.208
Is that possible?

41:12.250 --> 41:13.458
Why not?

41:13.500 --> 41:15.542
It's a machine, isn't it?

41:15.583 --> 41:17.125
Shut it off.

41:17.166 --> 41:21.208
Why? You haven't seen half

41:17.166 --> 41:21.208
of what this beauty can do.

41:21.250 --> 41:22.625
We've seen enough.

41:24.291 --> 41:26.000
Does that mean

41:24.291 --> 41:26.000
you're going to buy it?

41:26.041 --> 41:27.875
Yes, yes!

41:26.041 --> 41:27.875
We've seen enough!

41:26.041 --> 41:27.875
You made a sale!

41:27.917 --> 41:29.625
You won't be sorry.

41:29.667 --> 41:31.667
Good! Now end

41:29.667 --> 41:31.667
the demonstration!

41:31.709 --> 41:33.000
Done.

41:40.250 --> 41:41.500
PICARD:

41:40.250 --> 41:41.500
Number One?

41:41.542 --> 41:42.792
Right here.

41:42.834 --> 41:44.500
(<i> sighs</i> )

41:44.542 --> 41:46.208
That was close.

41:46.250 --> 41:48.083
La Forge,

41:46.250 --> 41:48.083
everything's all right.

41:48.125 --> 41:49.375
We've neutralized it.

41:49.417 --> 41:50.750
(<i> crash</i> )

41:50.792 --> 41:52.125
It's great to hear

41:50.792 --> 41:52.125
your voice, Captain

41:52.166 --> 41:53.500
but we're a little busy

41:52.166 --> 41:53.500
right now.

41:53.542 --> 41:54.625
I'll get right back to you.

41:54.667 --> 41:55.875
Phasers at full

41:54.667 --> 41:55.875
readiness.

41:55.917 --> 41:57.333
Keep those shields

41:55.917 --> 41:57.333
at full power.

41:57.375 --> 41:58.959
Ahead one-quarter.

41:59.000 --> 42:01.333
Heading 25

41:59.000 --> 42:01.333
mark 300.

42:01.375 --> 42:02.583
Sir, that heading

42:01.375 --> 42:02.583
will take us further

42:02.625 --> 42:04.291
into the planet's atmosphere.

42:04.333 --> 42:06.083
That's correct. We're going

42:04.333 --> 42:06.083
to lose some maneuverability

42:06.125 --> 42:07.333
so keep a firm hand

42:06.125 --> 42:07.333
on the helm.

42:07.375 --> 42:09.041
Aye, sir.

42:09.083 --> 42:11.500
You hope our attacker will

42:09.083 --> 42:11.500
follow us into the atmosphere.

42:11.542 --> 42:12.917
I'm counting on it.

42:12.959 --> 42:14.792
Lian, scan for any

42:12.959 --> 42:14.792
air disruption or vortex.

42:14.834 --> 42:16.250
Cloak or no cloak

42:16.291 --> 42:17.792
we'll spot it by its turbulence.

42:17.834 --> 42:19.792
Worf, how fast

42:17.834 --> 42:19.792
can you get a

42:17.834 --> 42:19.792
phaser lock?

42:19.834 --> 42:21.166
Fast.

42:21.208 --> 42:22.667
Hull temperature 1,000 degrees

42:21.208 --> 42:22.667
and rising.

42:22.709 --> 42:24.000
Emergency power to deflectors.

42:24.041 --> 42:24.959
Velocity increasing.

42:25.000 --> 42:26.792
Steady as she goes.

42:33.041 --> 42:35.166
Hull temperature

42:33.041 --> 42:35.166
2,500 degrees.

42:35.208 --> 42:37.166
Deflectors nearing overload.

42:37.208 --> 42:38.250
(<i> fast beeping</i> )

42:38.291 --> 42:40.250
Sir, helm's going unresponsive.

42:40.291 --> 42:42.083
Can you compensate?

42:40.291 --> 42:42.083
Yes, sir, I can.

42:42.125 --> 42:43.959
Hull 3,000 degrees.

42:44.000 --> 42:45.166
Maintain heading.

42:45.208 --> 42:46.709
WORF:

42:45.208 --> 42:46.709
We're about to lose

42:46.750 --> 42:48.333
number four deflector.

42:48.375 --> 42:50.291
3,300 degrees.

42:50.333 --> 42:52.375
Deflector four

42:50.333 --> 42:52.375
is now inoperative.

42:52.417 --> 42:53.583
Turbulence to starboard!

42:58.375 --> 42:59.917
There he is!

42:59.959 --> 43:00.959
Scanners locked.

43:01.000 --> 43:01.917
Weapons locked.

43:01.959 --> 43:03.083
Fire!

43:08.417 --> 43:09.542
Got him!

43:09.583 --> 43:12.417
(<i> sighs</i> )

43:12.458 --> 43:15.125
Shields down.

43:15.166 --> 43:16.458
(<i> beeping</i> )

43:16.500 --> 43:18.125
Locked onto away team.

43:18.166 --> 43:20.166
Beaming them home now.

43:20.208 --> 43:22.083
Come to 40, mark 65.

43:22.125 --> 43:26.750
Ahead one-third,

43:22.125 --> 43:26.750
and assume a standard orbit.

43:26.792 --> 43:27.959
Standard orbit.

43:28.000 --> 43:29.500
Aye, sir.

43:29.542 --> 43:31.667
(<i> sighs</i> )

43:40.375 --> 43:41.792
Relinquishing command,

43:40.375 --> 43:41.792
Captain.

43:41.834 --> 43:43.250
As you were, Lieutenant.

43:43.291 --> 43:45.125
Sir?

43:45.166 --> 43:47.375
Mr. La Forge, when I left

43:45.166 --> 43:47.375
this ship, it was in one piece.

43:47.417 --> 43:49.250
I would appreciate

43:47.417 --> 43:49.250
your returning it to me

43:49.291 --> 43:51.166
in the same condition.

43:51.208 --> 43:52.375
You concur, Number One?

43:52.417 --> 43:53.917
Absolutely, sir.

43:56.709 --> 43:58.333
Lieutenant Solis

43:58.375 --> 44:01.250
plot a course to rendezvous

43:58.375 --> 44:01.250
with the Saucer Section.

44:01.291 --> 44:02.375
Sick Bay reports

44:02.417 --> 44:03.875
Dr. Crusher's

44:02.417 --> 44:03.875
going to be fine.

44:03.917 --> 44:07.458
Course plotted

44:03.917 --> 44:07.458
and laid in.

44:11.291 --> 44:13.542
Engage.
